Exercise #1:  Write a script in Python that stores the number 2 in a variable called x, 
the number 7 in a variable called y, and the number -10 in a variable called z.  Calculate each of the following.
A. x + y
B. y - z
C. z / x
What do you notice when doing C.?
Is it mathematically accurate?
If not, how can you fix it?
